<darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>&lt;I&gt;Prefer&lt;/I&gt; + noun/&lt;I&gt;-ing&lt;/I&gt;</title><sectiontitle>We use &lt;I&gt;prefer&lt;/I&gt; to talk about something we like more than another thing or things. Introduce the second noun with &lt;I&gt;to&lt;/I&gt;.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_9_3_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>She likes coffee but she loves tea.</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_9_3_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>She &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;prefers&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; tea &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;to&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; coffee.</text1a><text2>I like Mozart but I like Beethoven more.</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_9_3_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;prefer&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; Beethoven &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;to&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; Mozart.</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_9_3_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Use &lt;I&gt;prefer&lt;/I&gt; with a noun or with the &lt;I&gt;-ing&lt;/I&gt; form of a verb.</sectiontitle2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_9_3_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>I prefer &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;tea&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; to &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;coffee&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_9_3_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>We prefer &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;watching&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; films at home to &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;going&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;  to the cinema.</text4a></section><section><title>&lt;I&gt;Will&lt;/I&gt; for spontaneous decisions and offers</title><sectiontitle>We use &lt;I&gt;will&lt;/I&gt; + verb when we decide to do something or offer to do something at the same time as we are speaking.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_9_3_7.mp3</titlesound><text1>There's somebody knocking on the door.</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_9_3_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>I&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;'ll answer&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; it.</text1a><text2>Can somebody help me with these bags?</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_9_3_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>We&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;'ll do&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; it.</text2a><titlesound2>%undefined</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>%undefined</sectiontitle2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>%undefined</sound3><text3a>%undefined</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>%undefined</sound4><text4a>%undefined</text4a></section></grammar>